      "message": "Do you mean we need to check whether the last update is actually a GPU operation or not?\n\nActually the main point is that if we sync the CPU writable buffer here, it would need a stall because we cannot use `CopyResource` to copy `lastUpdatedStorage` -\u003e `CPUWritableConstantBuffer` directly.\n\nWe could only copy indirectly via:\n- `lastUpdatedStorage` -\u003e `stagingStorage`\n- `stagingStorage` -\u003e `CPUWritableConstantBuffer`.\nThe 2nd copy has to be done via mapping and it\u0027s a stall. So it\u0027s better to sync the GPU counterpart of constant buffer here. It will only need one `CopyResource` call.\n\nNo matter what the last update storage is, it will always be able to used as the source of `CopyResource`.\n\nSo if `CPUWritableConstantBuffer` is out of date, we sync its GPU counterpart instead:\n- `lastUpdatedStorage` -\u003e `GPUCopyDstConstantBuffer`",
      "parentUuid": "26c84ebe_04183df8",
